1
00:00:00,700 --> 00:00:04,568
Tash, would you move faster, we don’t have
anything ready for the grand opening yet!

2
00:00:04,593 --> 00:00:06,606
I know, I’m already panicking!

3
00:00:06,631 --> 00:00:07,631
Oh!

4
00:00:11,429 --> 00:00:13,742
Oh, kuya, look!

5
00:00:14,742 --> 00:00:15,788
Remember this?

6
00:00:16,045 --> 00:00:17,045
Oh, gosh.

7
00:00:17,319 --> 00:00:19,199
We’re never going to use that again.

8
00:00:19,345 --> 00:00:20,345
Exactly

9
00:00:20,713 --> 00:00:24,125
No matter what happens, never…

10
00:00:24,445 --> 00:00:25,445
…again

11
00:00:26,605 --> 00:00:30,143
Um, what’s the Japanese term
again about fixing

12
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:33,705
broken objects and
embracing its imperfections?

13
00:00:36,546 --> 00:00:37,633
Kin…

14
00:00:39,042 --> 00:00:40,042
Ah…

15
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:42,920
- Tsugi! Kintusi, yes, correct!
- Kintsugi!

16
00:00:42,945 --> 00:00:44,285
Look, kuya.

17
00:00:44,705 --> 00:00:49,823
If you don’t get your jokes right,
you might get expelled.

18
00:00:51,565 --> 00:00:53,298
You’re such a great sister!

19
00:01:57,871 --> 00:01:58,871
Mm, get me some water.

20
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,360
Dad, guess what?

21
00:02:03,322 --> 00:02:05,601
I asked for vacation
to be extended here!

22
00:02:05,909 --> 00:02:09,409
Especially since your
birthday is coming up!

23
00:02:09,434 --> 00:02:11,311
- Wow!
- Yay!

24
00:02:11,371 --> 00:02:13,659
- Really?
- Yes, really!

25
00:02:13,684 --> 00:02:16,183
You heard what I told my boss,
didn’t you?

26
00:02:16,456 --> 00:02:19,249
You’re such an imitation artist, Tash!

27
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,873
What an early morning basher!

28
00:02:22,143 --> 00:02:25,070
- Oh!
- Stop it, don’t!

29
00:02:26,853 --> 00:02:30,233
No, but really,
I just want to thank you all,

30
00:02:30,738 --> 00:02:32,902
because you know this
is simply what I want.

31
00:02:33,515 --> 00:02:38,680
This simple get together because
you know we don’t have much.

32
00:02:40,209 --> 00:02:42,892
So thank you, thank you very much.
I’m genuinely happy.

33
00:02:42,917 --> 00:02:44,768
That’s okay, my love.

34
00:02:44,798 --> 00:02:48,057
What’s important is we’re all together.

35
00:02:50,381 --> 00:02:54,246
You know what, that’s perfect,
because I’m inviting my amigas over!

36
00:02:55,120 --> 00:03:00,534
Lola Maxi, what did I just say?
I just said we don’t have enough.

37
00:03:00,559 --> 00:03:04,286
The one we shouldn’t
be inviting are those two!

38
00:03:04,311 --> 00:03:06,228
Would you look at them?!

39
00:03:06,393 --> 00:03:10,002
Lola Maxi, we’re losing appetite
with what you’re saying.

40
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:12,435
He’s right! You’re too much!

41
00:03:13,349 --> 00:03:14,349
But this is too good.

42
00:03:14,382 --> 00:03:16,135
Okay, okay, let’s eat here!

43
00:03:20,278 --> 00:03:21,405
What’s this?!

44
00:03:26,478 --> 00:03:27,885
The spatula!

45
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:30,704
What?!
Kuya we heard something snap!

46
00:03:31,339 --> 00:03:32,672
Was it your bones?

47
00:03:32,757 --> 00:03:34,396
Bones?! What bones?!
Do you think I still have them?

48
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:37,146
Of course you do, look here, your elbows!

49
00:03:37,171 --> 00:03:38,435
My spatula!

50
00:03:40,747 --> 00:03:42,920
It snapped in half…
you should throw that away.

51
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:44,922
What do you mean throw it away?
I can’t throw this away!

52
00:03:44,947 --> 00:03:47,239
- What’s gotten into you!
- You’ve got no more use for that,

53
00:03:47,263 --> 00:03:48,761
what else can you use it for
when it’s already broken in half?

54
00:03:48,806 --> 00:03:50,371
Throw it away, that’s useless!

55
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:53,347
I can’t throw this away easily, this has
been with me for a very long time already.

56
00:03:53,372 --> 00:03:54,979
Look at you, you really
don’t know how to save up!

57
00:03:55,004 --> 00:03:56,012
What do you mean I don’t
know how to save up?!

58
00:03:56,037 --> 00:03:58,585
Watch your words…be
careful with your words.

59
00:03:58,618 --> 00:04:00,065
Oh, by the way…

60
00:04:01,522 --> 00:04:02,808
What are you wearing?!

61
00:04:02,963 --> 00:04:06,137
Because I’m trying to dry my pants here!

62
00:04:09,226 --> 00:04:13,907
Ow! It’s hot! I forgot.

63
00:04:13,932 --> 00:04:15,338
What are you doing?

64
00:04:15,471 --> 00:04:16,471
This!

65
00:04:30,793 --> 00:04:32,247
I’m so glad this dried up!

66
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,272
The forecast said it’s going
to be raining frequently!

67
00:04:34,605 --> 00:04:36,438
Oh, see, the pandesal pieces are done!

68
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:39,633
What are you doing, Iskineport?!

69
00:04:39,658 --> 00:04:41,753
Everything, I’m doing everything…

70
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:46,453
Why doesn’t this want to adhere?!

71
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,668
- Why?!
- Dad, what’s that?

72
00:04:48,693 --> 00:04:50,950
It’s so simple taking care of this, but…

73
00:04:51,837 --> 00:04:52,837
What is that?

74
00:04:52,862 --> 00:04:55,744
What do you mean? This is broken, look,
and i’m trying to fix it!

75
00:04:55,898 --> 00:04:58,611
Dad, I’ll just get you
a new spatula online.

76
00:04:58,636 --> 00:05:00,116
I want this spatula.

77
00:05:00,226 --> 00:05:02,080
Dad, how are you going to fix that?

78
00:05:02,504 --> 00:05:04,071
- I’ll fix it.
- What is this – shoe lace?

79
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,249
- Those aren’t shoe laces!
- Tito,

80
00:05:05,282 --> 00:05:08,725
there are many better and
more high tech spatulas out there.

81
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:12,375
You three, you all sound the same.
I’m just noticing.

82
00:05:13,913 --> 00:05:14,913
- What’s that about?
- What?

83
00:05:15,093 --> 00:05:16,646
You all sound like…

84
00:05:19,334 --> 00:05:20,334
Hoo!

85
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:21,487
Chef K!

86
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:26,250
I really don’t understand it.

87
00:05:27,365 --> 00:05:30,158
I can’t think of any reason
why Chacha liked you.

88
00:05:31,315 --> 00:05:33,961
You’re ugly, and now I
can see you’re cheap!

89
00:05:34,841 --> 00:05:36,048
All of you, listen to this.

90
00:05:37,082 --> 00:05:42,107
A soldier’s wife
is like his weapon.

91
00:05:42,972 --> 00:05:44,412
It’s the same way for this.

92
00:05:44,604 --> 00:05:48,210
He won’t replace his weapon,
he won’t leave his weapon.

93
00:05:48,535 --> 00:05:50,241
It’s that simple.

94
00:05:50,423 --> 00:05:51,423
Well, are you a soldier?

95
00:05:51,656 --> 00:05:53,196
- No!
- Exactly the point!

96
00:05:53,464 --> 00:05:55,344
You have no match for my body!

97
00:05:57,563 --> 00:06:06,992
No match, see? See, see?!
Strong and firm! Look!

98
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:08,325
Hey!

99
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:10,346
Oh, strong.

100
00:06:11,039 --> 00:06:12,039
You hit me!

101
00:06:12,058 --> 00:06:13,330
Is the strength here in the room with us?

102
00:06:13,355 --> 00:06:15,226
- Why did you hit me?
- You said you were strong!

103
00:06:15,513 --> 00:06:17,213
- Yeah, that was strong!
- Okay, then I’m sorry!

104
00:06:23,973 --> 00:06:25,368
- What happened?
- It’s Iskineport!

105
00:06:25,393 --> 00:06:26,799
- What about Iskineport?!
- He got into an accident!

106
00:06:27,673 --> 00:06:28,780
He hit me again!

107
00:06:31,382 --> 00:06:32,762
Once again!

108
00:06:34,314 --> 00:06:35,354
Why was he hitting me?

109
00:06:36,003 --> 00:06:37,916
Well this is expensive!
Isn’t there anything cheaper than this?

110
00:06:38,478 --> 00:06:39,678
Keep your mouth shut about this.

111
00:06:41,343 --> 00:06:45,355
This is a five peso
sachet of uncooked rice.

112
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,070
Great!

113
00:06:47,095 --> 00:06:49,262
This is exactly what I’m looking for!

114
00:06:49,287 --> 00:06:50,739
Right?! That’s a winner!

115
00:06:50,764 --> 00:06:53,373
Tell Barangay Cinco that
I’m your source, yeah?

116
00:06:53,398 --> 00:06:55,344
You got it! I’ll let everyone know!

117
00:06:56,994 --> 00:06:58,094
Finally we were able to sell!

118
00:06:58,119 --> 00:07:00,965
Hey, Beauty!

119
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,811
- What’s up, Kuya Aga?
- Mariposa!

120
00:07:02,836 --> 00:07:04,855
Hey, Kuya Aga! What’s up?

121
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,880
Nothing.

122
00:07:05,905 --> 00:07:07,452
I actually forgot why I was here.

123
00:07:07,498 --> 00:07:08,996
- Beauty!
- Yes, kuya?

124
00:07:09,021 --> 00:07:10,021
Do you have alcohol?

125
00:07:10,244 --> 00:07:11,464
- Alcohol?
- Alcohol?

126
00:07:11,489 --> 00:07:12,489
Alcohol.

127
00:07:15,983 --> 00:07:16,983
You want hard?

128
00:07:17,008 --> 00:07:18,724
Alcohol, I’m gonna go buy alcohol.

129
00:07:18,749 --> 00:07:21,929
Iskineport got into an accident,
I’m applying first aid on him.

130
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:28,389
I thought we were gonna get lucky!

131
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:30,691
- Kuya Aga,
- Yeah?

132
00:07:30,716 --> 00:07:33,557
It’s a shame you’re gonna break
your annual tradition

133
00:07:33,582 --> 00:07:35,350
for your birthday
here in the barangay.

134
00:07:35,472 --> 00:07:36,843
- Oh, the little party with food?
- Yes.

135
00:07:37,136 --> 00:07:39,854
- Party with food?!
- Where at?!

136
00:07:40,431 --> 00:07:41,897
Do you have lumpia?

137
00:07:42,191 --> 00:07:46,675
This is what I’m talking about!
I apologize, you know me.

138
00:07:47,134 --> 00:07:48,581
If I have the money,
I wouldn’t even think

139
00:07:48,605 --> 00:07:50,301
twice about sharing, I
will share my blessings.

140
00:07:50,326 --> 00:07:52,991
But you can see what’s been
going on with my life recently,

141
00:07:53,016 --> 00:07:58,014
the store is going bankrupt,
the bakery is…doesn’t matter.

142
00:07:59,629 --> 00:08:02,472
Don’t worry about it,
once I get enough…

143
00:08:03,598 --> 00:08:04,865
look at these guys.

144
00:08:07,604 --> 00:08:10,268
Alright, alright, I’ll get a
party together, with food and alcohol!

145
00:08:10,293 --> 00:08:11,293
Oh, we’re eating now?!

146
00:08:18,003 --> 00:08:21,697
When I get the money!
But not that I don’t, thank you for now!

147
00:08:21,722 --> 00:08:23,244
Get a load of this guy! Let’s just go.

148
00:08:23,297 --> 00:08:24,711
Oh, no food. Okay, then!

149
00:08:25,134 --> 00:08:26,992
That’s what I’ve been saying!
Be careful, slowly!

150
00:08:27,017 --> 00:08:28,563
- Ow!
- Careful!

151
00:08:28,588 --> 00:08:30,408
- Hey, hey!
- Ow!

152
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:31,807
I said slowly!

153
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:32,958
Look!

154
00:08:34,227 --> 00:08:37,323
Why on earth do we have to tether
my hand to this piece of wood?!

155
00:08:37,348 --> 00:08:39,048
So it won’t move!

156
00:08:39,194 --> 00:08:40,347
- That’s correct!
- See, try now! Can you move it?

157
00:08:40,682 --> 00:08:42,749
I obviously can’t!
How am I supposed to move with this?!

158
00:08:42,774 --> 00:08:44,457
The question is how did you manage
to get burned like that?

159
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,907
I accidentally went
too close to the furnace.

160
00:08:47,971 --> 00:08:49,029
What were you thinking,
you genius?

161
00:08:49,054 --> 00:08:50,991
Of course you’re gonna get burned
when you stand too close!

162
00:08:51,663 --> 00:08:54,536
Iskineport, you should always be careful.

163
00:08:55,274 --> 00:08:56,027
I know, I know.

164
00:08:56,052 --> 00:08:57,609
This is what I’m talking about.

165
00:08:57,664 --> 00:09:01,009
This is just perfect timing

166
00:09:01,034 --> 00:09:04,386
I broke my spatula,
and now you just got into an accident.

167
00:09:04,719 --> 00:09:07,752
What about my accident?
I can still work, I can still help!

168
00:09:15,517 --> 00:09:16,517
Miss?

169
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,040
Miss?

170
00:09:19,413 --> 00:09:20,727
Are you okay? Are you okay?

171
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:22,470
Are you okay?

172
00:09:22,717 --> 00:09:25,850
Ah, yes. I’m okay.

173
00:09:25,917 --> 00:09:27,697
Do you have drinking water?

174
00:09:27,722 --> 00:09:31,273
Oh, water, yeah! Chard, get me water,
a glass of water! Quick! Come on!

175
00:09:34,357 --> 00:09:35,854
- Because!
- What was that?!

176
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:37,132
Oh, what’s happening now?!

177
00:09:37,398 --> 00:09:38,398
Water, get me water!

178
00:09:38,423 --> 00:09:39,832
Water, faster, faster!

179
00:09:39,878 --> 00:09:42,537
What’s happening, what’s happening?!

180
00:09:42,562 --> 00:09:43,679
Oh goodness, why is this happening?

181
00:09:44,298 --> 00:09:46,818
Looks like a choosey one!

182
00:09:46,843 --> 00:09:49,120
She was about to fall against Ate Cha,
but now look she chose to fall on you!

183
00:09:49,145 --> 00:09:51,899
What am I supposed to do, she fell on me,
she was dizzy! She collapsed!

184
00:09:51,948 --> 00:09:53,174
- Really, now?
- Yeah!

185
00:09:55,988 --> 00:09:58,661
Um, what happened?

186
00:09:58,988 --> 00:10:01,659
What happened?
You almost got my wife to kill me.

187
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:03,567
No, what I mean is you fainted!

188
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,400
You did!

189
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:08,337
- Are you good?
- Are you okay?

190
00:10:09,983 --> 00:10:12,415
- I’m still feeling a little bit dizzy.
- Gosh!

191
00:10:12,453 --> 00:10:14,699
Maybe it’s because I haven’t eaten!

192
00:10:14,724 --> 00:10:17,065
Oh! Food, food!
Chard, get her something to eat!

193
00:10:17,089 --> 00:10:18,436
Get her an ensaymada!

194
00:10:18,643 --> 00:10:20,313
- Quick!
- Is your name OA?!

195
00:10:20,735 --> 00:10:22,063
- You’re too much.
- Here!

196
00:10:22,088 --> 00:10:23,954
- Sweetie, sweetie, here you go, eat.
- Eat up.

197
00:10:24,481 --> 00:10:26,008
Thank you.

198
00:10:27,850 --> 00:10:29,249
Kuya Aga, Ate Cha,

199
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:31,273
I pity her.

200
00:10:32,522 --> 00:10:35,912
Could we let her stay here for now?
The streets are dangerous now.

201
00:10:36,452 --> 00:10:38,418
She could get in trouble
for all we know.

202
00:10:38,515 --> 00:10:39,515
You know how dangerous it is.

203
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:41,933
Um, Mika.
What exactly are you here for?

204
00:10:42,336 --> 00:10:44,763
I’m looking for a job.

205
00:10:46,566 --> 00:10:47,600
Okay, see!

206
00:10:48,145 --> 00:10:51,838
Let her stay here
until she can find a job!

207
00:10:52,131 --> 00:10:53,857
What are your skills?
What do you know to do?

208
00:10:53,886 --> 00:10:55,733
I used to be an assistant baker.

209
00:10:55,786 --> 00:10:57,626
I know how to operate a furnace!

210
00:10:57,710 --> 00:10:59,176
- Furnace operator?!
- That’s so cool!

211
00:10:59,201 --> 00:11:00,744
That’s perfect!

212
00:11:01,792 --> 00:11:04,152
Why don’t you leave now?
You mean you want to stay here, too?!

213
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:06,250
Now you want to
replace me for my job?!

214
00:11:06,275 --> 00:11:07,449
Look at you, Iskineport!

215
00:11:07,474 --> 00:11:10,081
Just because we were talking about your
position, you suddenly change your mind!

216
00:11:10,348 --> 00:11:12,301
Sweetie, you’re hired.

217
00:11:12,326 --> 00:11:14,316
See! You’re… hired? Hang on!

218
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:15,661
We don’t have anything
to pay her salary with!

219
00:11:15,686 --> 00:11:19,005
Her timing is actually perfect!

220
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:22,927
Iskineport just got into an accident,
and you have so many orders to fulfill.

221
00:11:23,170 --> 00:11:26,050
So, Mika, you’re hired!

222
00:11:26,075 --> 00:11:27,913
Welcome to Bake Haus of U!

223
00:11:29,301 --> 00:11:30,303
Really?!

224
00:11:30,451 --> 00:11:31,451
Yes!

225
00:11:31,476 --> 00:11:32,704
Thank you very much!

226
00:11:34,002 --> 00:11:35,002
Thank you!

227
00:11:35,263 --> 00:11:36,843
Okay, okay, you’re welcome!

228
00:11:37,516 --> 00:11:39,175
Thank you so much, really!

229
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,069
She’s hugging me! She is!

230
00:11:41,539 --> 00:11:44,547
Kuya, we really need to
help Dad with his spatula.

231
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,927
Okay, then let’s get him a new one!

232
00:11:47,237 --> 00:11:49,674
- OMG, didn’t you hear him?
- What, what?

233
00:11:49,699 --> 00:11:50,888
- Why?
- He doesn’t want to replace it.

234
00:11:50,913 --> 00:11:52,773
Well do you have any
other plans in mind, Tash?

235
00:11:55,808 --> 00:11:57,495
Here, my spatulas!

236
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,520
Here, look!

237
00:11:58,545 --> 00:12:01,859
I have metal, plastic, rubber!

238
00:12:01,964 --> 00:12:05,636
That’s expensive and good quality!

239
00:12:05,947 --> 00:12:08,080
I asked Chef K for help.

240
00:12:08,656 --> 00:12:12,312
Thank you, Chef K!
Hopefully this helps out Dad!

241
00:12:12,608 --> 00:12:13,928
Thank you very much!

242
00:12:13,953 --> 00:12:15,705
Well of course, I am a chef!

243
00:12:16,028 --> 00:12:20,368
I really don’t know about your Dad,
I’m not like him, quoting soldiers!

244
00:12:20,896 --> 00:12:21,896
Well, meow!

245
00:12:23,096 --> 00:12:27,320
If I were your Daddy, you wouldn’t be
having any of these problems.

246
00:12:27,345 --> 00:12:29,619
Thank you so much, Chef K.
Thank you so much.

247
00:12:29,644 --> 00:12:31,598
Really, thank you so much, Chef K.

248
00:12:31,628 --> 00:12:33,710
- Uh, Dad. You can also call me Dad.
- Oh…

249
00:12:33,735 --> 00:12:36,091
- Just call me Dad.
- Oh, okay, okay. Okay. Thank you, Chef K!

250
00:12:36,116 --> 00:12:38,058
- Thank you!
- Thank you for the spatula!

251
00:12:39,281 --> 00:12:40,281
Welp, meow!

252
00:12:40,306 --> 00:12:44,500
What’s gotten into you?!
You keep meowing, are you a cat?!

253
00:12:44,836 --> 00:12:46,716
Stop it, you’re annoying me!

254
00:12:46,741 --> 00:12:47,838
Here, look, there’s two…

255
00:12:48,186 --> 00:12:49,186
Thank you!

256
00:12:51,314 --> 00:12:52,314
Bye!

257
00:12:53,589 --> 00:12:54,895
What can I do for you? What do you want?

258
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,171
- Ensaymada.
- Ensaymada?

259
00:12:56,552 --> 00:12:57,557
Thank you!

260
00:12:57,582 --> 00:12:59,859
Wow, this is a good spot for chilling.
Can we take a picture?

261
00:12:59,978 --> 00:13:02,665
Oh wow, a selfie now, huh?

262
00:13:02,748 --> 00:13:04,012
- You’re very pretty!
- Careful!

263
00:13:12,798 --> 00:13:14,265
Are you guys okay there?

264
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:15,980
Is it good?

265
00:13:18,232 --> 00:13:19,232
Wow!

266
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,936
Chacha, looks like you’ve leveled up!

267
00:13:21,962 --> 00:13:23,822
Pretty long line you got there,
looks like a box-office hit!

268
00:13:23,847 --> 00:13:26,050
Hey, who is this?

269
00:13:27,547 --> 00:13:29,394
Is this your husband’s mistress?

270
00:13:29,677 --> 00:13:30,677
What?

271
00:13:31,257 --> 00:13:34,810
Oh, so-sorry! I meant new staff,
your husband’s new staff.

272
00:13:34,961 --> 00:13:36,427
Oh, okay!

273
00:13:36,452 --> 00:13:38,065
Um, Mika, this is
Chef K.

274
00:13:38,089 --> 00:13:41,822
He owns the bakery across the street,
the Bake K Nemen.

275
00:13:43,085 --> 00:13:46,418
Oh yeah, I know him!

276
00:13:46,588 --> 00:13:47,588
- You do?
- Don’t we?

277
00:13:47,613 --> 00:13:49,540
You know each other already?

278
00:13:49,931 --> 00:13:53,804
Oh, yeah!
Because she applied to me first.

279
00:13:54,015 --> 00:13:56,515
Then I told her to apply
to your bake shop instead.

280
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,808
Oh, okay.

281
00:13:58,954 --> 00:14:00,521
Kuya, ensaymada?

282
00:14:00,922 --> 00:14:02,156
I don’t want that.

283
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:03,628
I want Miss Sexy.

284
00:14:04,614 --> 00:14:07,189
Are you sure with your decision
when you accepted that woman?

285
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:09,506
Creeps and perverts have been coming
and going since she started working here.

286
00:14:11,699 --> 00:14:16,973
Sweetie, you give this out to them,
otherwise, I might bury this guy alive.

287
00:14:19,970 --> 00:14:21,530
Oh, beautiful eyes!

288
00:14:21,555 --> 00:14:24,411
Ew! Stop, you’re making me cringe!

289
00:14:26,854 --> 00:14:27,854
- Thank you, Kuya!
- Here’s my payment.

290
00:14:28,736 --> 00:14:29,736
And here’s for you.

291
00:14:29,742 --> 00:14:31,689
- Oh, a tip now, huh?!
- Thank you!

292
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,687
What was that? Another ensaymada?

293
00:14:37,973 --> 00:14:39,013
Thank you!

294
00:14:41,850 --> 00:14:42,916
- Kuya!
- Yes?

295
00:14:42,947 --> 00:14:44,617
You closed it! Didn’t you see?!

296
00:14:44,642 --> 00:14:46,113
- I’m sorry!
- Ensaymada…

297
00:14:46,138 --> 00:14:47,138
There!

298
00:14:47,373 --> 00:14:48,419
It is true!

299
00:14:49,158 --> 00:14:51,932
There are so many customers now, look!

300
00:14:53,067 --> 00:14:54,067
Mika!

301
00:14:55,093 --> 00:14:56,917
Mika, you know what
I feel like you’ve got some

302
00:14:56,948 --> 00:14:58,778
luck in your step and
you brought it right to us.

303
00:14:58,827 --> 00:15:01,727
You really call it luck?
Couldn’t that be just beginner’s luck?

304
00:15:03,153 --> 00:15:06,345
Why can’t you just be happy
that we have lots of customers!

305
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,266
Look at you!
Don’t you want this?

306
00:15:10,188 --> 00:15:12,528
You’ll get more time to rest!

307
00:15:12,553 --> 00:15:13,768
I’m well-rested enough,
I don’t need rest!

308
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:15,791
Hmmm.

309
00:15:16,571 --> 00:15:17,902
Oh! Oh!

310
00:15:18,295 --> 00:15:19,462
Are you alright?!

311
00:15:19,856 --> 00:15:23,143
Um, I think I’m feeling dizzy again!

312
00:15:23,168 --> 00:15:27,003
Ah, Cha? Is that okay with you?
That’s okay?

313
00:15:27,499 --> 00:15:28,625
She’s dizzy!

314
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:29,830
Ate Cha!

315
00:15:30,056 --> 00:15:31,583
- It’s time!
- What?!

316
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:34,708
No,

317
00:15:35,991 --> 00:15:37,784
it’s different. It’s still different.

318
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,269
This one’s hard to use.

319
00:15:39,435 --> 00:15:43,163
This is better, it doesn’t break, see?
Look, look!

320
00:15:44,674 --> 00:15:46,513
But nothing beats my spatula.

321
00:15:46,538 --> 00:15:48,231
The real one, the one that’s mine!

322
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:51,426
Dad, your spatula’s already retired.

323
00:15:51,558 --> 00:15:53,798
- Hmm?
- Move on to a new one.

324
00:15:54,391 --> 00:15:55,391
You know,

325
00:15:55,443 --> 00:15:59,103
you should also
give up on your dad.

326
00:15:59,836 --> 00:16:01,149
Dad, there’s a new one.

327
00:16:01,646 --> 00:16:04,574
It’s better than the old one
because they’ve improved it.

328
00:16:05,001 --> 00:16:06,574
Yeah, yeah.

329
00:16:07,031 --> 00:16:08,031
Kintsugi!

330
00:16:08,616 --> 00:16:09,689
Kintsugi?

331
00:16:09,809 --> 00:16:10,809
Kintsugi!

332
00:16:11,348 --> 00:16:16,815
It’s the art from Japan where they
fix broken things using gold or silver.

333
00:16:17,269 --> 00:16:22,031
The stuff that’s shattered and you
think it’s worthless—after they fix it,

334
00:16:22,593 --> 00:16:24,959
it becomes more valuable.

335
00:16:25,137 --> 00:16:26,137
That’s it!

336
00:16:26,162 --> 00:16:27,969
Dad, what does that have
to do with your spatula?

337
00:16:27,994 --> 00:16:29,162
Why are you getting upset?

338
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:31,429
No, because your spatula!

339
00:16:33,008 --> 00:16:35,588
But your spatula
isn’t an art piece, Dad.

340
00:16:35,613 --> 00:16:36,774
What do you mean, not an art piece?

341
00:16:36,827 --> 00:16:39,540
To you, it’s worthless, but to me,

342
00:16:39,565 --> 00:16:43,184
it’s been with me through my tough years,
all the way till now.

343
00:16:43,778 --> 00:16:45,531
Ah!

344
00:16:45,556 --> 00:16:50,821
So that’s why Grandpa Roman
always has stuff repaired!

345
00:16:51,008 --> 00:16:52,840
- Repaired?
- Repaired what?

346
00:16:52,865 --> 00:16:54,213
What does Grandpa repair?

347
00:16:54,331 --> 00:16:55,717
Well, his underwear!

348
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:58,143
Lola Maxi!

349
00:16:58,876 --> 00:17:02,098
- Here we go again!
- But didn’t you say, “tsugi”? “Tsugi”!

350
00:17:02,123 --> 00:17:06,640
His underwear’s been “tsugi’d”! When your
underwear’s “tsugi’d,” don’t you repair it?

351
00:17:06,665 --> 00:17:07,853
Oh my gosh, Lola Maxi!

352
00:17:07,878 --> 00:17:10,589
Alright, drop your contributions, everyone!

353
00:17:11,894 --> 00:17:13,194
Come on, now!

354
00:17:13,491 --> 00:17:15,178
Oh, for Kuya Aga!

355
00:17:15,244 --> 00:17:16,844
Thank you, thank you!

356
00:17:17,524 --> 00:17:19,117
Contributions for Kuya Aga!

357
00:17:19,142 --> 00:17:20,188
Mariposa!

358
00:17:20,213 --> 00:17:21,534
Boss- Boss Beauty!

359
00:17:21,559 --> 00:17:23,125
Isn’t that backwards?

360
00:17:23,484 --> 00:17:25,584
Shouldn’t Kuya Aga
be the one paying?

361
00:17:25,637 --> 00:17:27,197
What are you talking about, Mariposa?!

362
00:17:27,490 --> 00:17:29,657
Kuya Aga is such a nice person to us.

363
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:32,953
What’s wrong with giving him
a simple celebration?

364
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:35,183
Well, I guess you have a point.

365
00:17:35,572 --> 00:17:38,449
Da Pers Family has done
so much for our barangay.

366
00:17:38,474 --> 00:17:40,999
- True, you’re right! Right?!
- Yeah, that’s true.

367
00:17:41,050 --> 00:17:42,597
That’s why we should chip in.

368
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:43,990
Promise, later.

369
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:46,989
So, how much is it now?

370
00:17:47,014 --> 00:17:48,014
Not much yet.

371
00:17:49,226 --> 00:17:50,226
What happened here?

372
00:17:50,239 --> 00:17:51,625
- Oh!
- Oh!

373
00:17:51,650 --> 00:17:54,980
There’s wood…
You know there’s wood here!

374
00:17:55,548 --> 00:17:58,770
Wait, why does your face
look like you’re about to cry?

375
00:17:58,821 --> 00:18:03,125
Well, at Kuya Aga’s place,
they’ve got a new staff member.

376
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:06,817
And this Iskineport guy is about to be
replaced, because he’s just so beautiful!

377
00:18:06,925 --> 00:18:07,925
He’s even sexy!

378
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,733
A lot of people are lining up
at the bakery now!

379
00:18:11,401 --> 00:18:12,401
You know,

380
00:18:12,779 --> 00:18:15,378
I have a bad feeling about Mika.

381
00:18:15,696 --> 00:18:17,016
She’s a bad person!

382
00:18:17,368 --> 00:18:19,042
A bad person, but that beautiful?

383
00:18:19,617 --> 00:18:23,062
If you were in Kuya Aga’s shoes and
you had to choose between yourself

384
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,966
who’s ugly or Mika,
who’s beautiful and also

385
00:18:25,991 --> 00:18:28,277
stronger with customers,
what would you pick?

386
00:18:28,739 --> 00:18:30,849
Did you just say I’m ugly?!

387
00:18:30,874 --> 00:18:32,205
You know, Chard is right.

388
00:18:32,695 --> 00:18:36,329
But sometimes,
even if something’s all torn and stinky,

389
00:18:37,627 --> 00:18:38,953
you don’t replace it right away.

390
00:18:39,164 --> 00:18:40,164
Wow!

391
00:18:40,423 --> 00:18:43,202
You just called me ugly,
but you’re so good-looking.

392
00:18:43,369 --> 00:18:45,503
And you—ugh, you stink.

393
00:18:45,528 --> 00:18:47,742
Your breath stinks, too!

394
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,080
Hoo!

395
00:18:49,105 --> 00:18:51,123
That’s too much, come on!

396
00:18:51,148 --> 00:18:52,621
Wow, smells like sewer!

397
00:18:52,717 --> 00:18:56,965
But guys, guys, sometimes
love isn’t everything, you know.

398
00:18:57,377 --> 00:19:00,613
Sometimes, you need to be practical too.

399
00:19:00,638 --> 00:19:03,346
When you don’t need something anymore,
just throw it away.

400
00:19:03,371 --> 00:19:04,371
True, you’ve got a point.

401
00:19:04,672 --> 00:19:08,773
So, does that mean I’m no longer
needed and should just be thrown away?

402
00:19:08,997 --> 00:19:15,560
Speaking of practical,
Kuya Aga’s really practical.

403
00:19:15,957 --> 00:19:19,124
He wouldn’t just let me go,
he wouldn’t kick me out.

404
00:19:19,406 --> 00:19:21,059
My Kuya Aga loves me, you know.

405
00:19:21,298 --> 00:19:23,012
But sometimes, love is like that, right?

406
00:19:23,591 --> 00:19:26,457
When you love someone,
even if they’re ugly!

407
00:19:26,951 --> 00:19:27,951
Ugly!

408
00:19:28,239 --> 00:19:29,638
You’re blind to it
because you love them.

409
00:19:29,703 --> 00:19:33,113
You guys are confusing me!
I really don’t know what’s going to happen.

410
00:19:33,566 --> 00:19:36,847
I don’t know if Kuya Aga
is going to keep me or not!

411
00:19:37,925 --> 00:19:41,557
Chef K, it seems like Ate Cha
isn’t even jealous.

412
00:19:42,339 --> 00:19:45,649
Oh, that just means
you’re not doing enough.

413
00:19:47,995 --> 00:19:49,428
I think I’m done.

414
00:19:50,634 --> 00:19:53,080
Their family’s so nice to me.

415
00:19:53,105 --> 00:19:55,944
No, you can’t quit!

416
00:19:56,377 --> 00:19:57,836
You have to do this!

417
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,596
Listen to me carefully.

418
00:20:00,038 --> 00:20:04,394
If you get that couple to fight,
you’ll be square with me.

419
00:20:04,855 --> 00:20:05,855
We’ll be even.

420
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:08,130
Can I pay you with
something else?

421
00:20:08,404 --> 00:20:10,037
A massage, maybe?

422
00:20:10,454 --> 00:20:11,901
Hard or soft?

423
00:20:12,925 --> 00:20:14,438
Ugh, I don’t like that.

424
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:17,624
It tickles me! It tickles me,
and besides, I’m not into you!

425
00:20:17,649 --> 00:20:18,649
Stop it already!

426
00:20:22,291 --> 00:20:23,411
Let’s go with Plan B.

427
00:20:24,940 --> 00:20:26,073
What am I supposed to do?

428
00:20:26,753 --> 00:20:27,753
Plan B.

429
00:20:27,778 --> 00:20:28,778
Do you see this?

430
00:20:29,970 --> 00:20:30,970
What’s this?

431
00:20:32,747 --> 00:20:33,807
Spy camera.

432
00:20:34,226 --> 00:20:35,762
- No way.
- Yes.

433
00:20:37,563 --> 00:20:38,563
So, you know.

434
00:21:00,001 --> 00:21:01,547
Ow! You just hit me!

435
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:08,051
Aha!

436
00:21:09,406 --> 00:21:11,413
We caught you red-handed!

437
00:21:11,878 --> 00:21:15,691
You're setting that up, huh?!
That camera!

438
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:17,211
- That’s a camera?!
- Yes!

439
00:21:17,236 --> 00:21:18,236
What?!

440
00:21:18,537 --> 00:21:21,070
- I just came to borrow some sugar!
- Sugar?!

441
00:21:21,095 --> 00:21:23,207
Then why are you
setting this up, huh?!

442
00:21:23,509 --> 00:21:24,509
It’s a camera!

443
00:21:24,584 --> 00:21:26,504
You were right, Iskineport!

444
00:21:26,529 --> 00:21:27,529
See? It’s true!

445
00:21:27,831 --> 00:21:32,531
Oh, you’ve got something
planned for Kuya Aga, huh?!

446
00:21:32,556 --> 00:21:33,636
You’re in big trouble now!

447
00:21:33,661 --> 00:21:35,575
- You’re finished!
- You’re done!

448
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,845
Here, take this–

449
00:21:36,870 --> 00:21:38,716
Don’t look at me like that!

450
00:21:39,092 --> 00:21:44,549
I’m not falling for those…
wow, your eyes are beautiful.

451
00:21:44,574 --> 00:21:45,574
Right?!

452
00:21:45,756 --> 00:21:47,730
- No! No!
- Hey! Fight back, Iskineport!

453
00:21:50,044 --> 00:21:51,124
Hey! What’s going on here?!

454
00:21:51,437 --> 00:21:52,490
Mika, what are you doing here?

455
00:21:52,515 --> 00:21:55,801
Kuya, we saw them
setting up this camera here!

456
00:21:55,832 --> 00:22:01,276
Kuya Aga, Ate Cha! I caught them
setting up a camera to spy on me!

457
00:22:01,301 --> 00:22:03,618
What are you saying?!

458
00:22:03,643 --> 00:22:05,314
Don’t lie!

459
00:22:05,781 --> 00:22:07,461
It wasn’t us, Kuya!
It was her first!

460
00:22:07,486 --> 00:22:09,552
Iskineport, why are you
holding that camera?

461
00:22:09,584 --> 00:22:14,126
No, Kuya, when we came in,
we saw her holding it!

462
00:22:14,151 --> 00:22:16,389
Alright, let’s not talk about
this anymore. Go home.

463
00:22:16,426 --> 00:22:18,586
- Fine.
- We’ll talk about it tomorrow.

464
00:22:18,611 --> 00:22:19,611
Geez!

465
00:22:19,918 --> 00:22:24,725
Kuya, I did everything
to protect you from this…

466
00:22:24,749 --> 00:22:27,093
and this is what you do to us?

467
00:22:27,124 --> 00:22:28,737
Suspicious!

468
00:22:28,768 --> 00:22:31,013
- Me?!
- You don’t believe me!

469
00:22:31,092 --> 00:22:34,206
You’re too obsessed
with women like that, and

470
00:22:34,231 --> 00:22:36,618
that’s why you keep
messing up with your family!

471
00:22:37,029 --> 00:22:38,295
Messing up how?!

472
00:22:38,581 --> 00:22:41,198
This is ridiculous—it’s late already!

473
00:22:41,574 --> 00:22:44,147
Iskineport, Iskineport! Don’t–

474
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,280
Leave!

475
00:22:47,305 --> 00:22:50,236
Your knees are weak!

476
00:22:50,261 --> 00:22:52,629
Your heart is weak!

477
00:22:54,243 --> 00:22:57,263
Yeah! Quit sticking out your tongue,
it’s not working!

478
00:22:58,779 --> 00:23:00,112
This is unbelievable!

479
00:23:00,137 --> 00:23:03,270
It’s always women!
Women always mess you up!

480
00:23:03,361 --> 00:23:04,761
Women, women!

481
00:23:07,666 --> 00:23:08,859
Kuya Aga!

482
00:23:09,386 --> 00:23:11,268
Yeah? Go to sleep.

483
00:23:11,322 --> 00:23:12,322
I keep getting dragged into trouble.

484
00:23:12,347 --> 00:23:13,502
- Just go. Go to sleep.
- Good night.

485
00:23:13,527 --> 00:23:14,926
Ah, fine. Go to sleep, okay?

486
00:23:15,561 --> 00:23:16,828
Good night, good night, good night.

487
00:23:17,909 --> 00:23:19,356
- Let’s sleep, come on.
- What?

488
00:23:19,381 --> 00:23:21,453
- Let’s go to sleep.
- Oh, we’re sleeping now, too?

489
00:23:21,478 --> 00:23:23,346
- This is getting confusing.
- Alright–

490
00:23:47,245 --> 00:23:48,885
I’m giving up, Chef K.

491
00:23:49,336 --> 00:23:50,716
I’ll just pay off my debts.

492
00:23:50,975 --> 00:23:52,102
I’m done with this!

493
00:23:53,017 --> 00:23:54,017
Mika, what are you saying?!

494
00:23:54,379 --> 00:23:56,292
Now’s not the time to give up!

495
00:23:57,334 --> 00:23:58,334
I’ll take care of it.

496
00:23:58,500 --> 00:23:59,500
I’ve got your back!

497
00:23:59,831 --> 00:24:01,331
I can’t anymore. I’m done.

498
00:24:01,532 --> 00:24:02,532
I’m just going to confess.

499
00:24:04,802 --> 00:24:05,802
Mika?

500
00:24:07,757 --> 00:24:08,757
Mika!

501
00:24:10,583 --> 00:24:11,776
Where’s Iskineport?

502
00:24:13,464 --> 00:24:14,724
Ouch! Ouch!

503
00:24:15,604 --> 00:24:17,144
- My eye!
- What happened?

504
00:24:17,277 --> 00:24:20,897
- Kuya Aga, something got in my eye.
- What happened to you?

505
00:24:20,950 --> 00:24:21,950
Where? Here? Here?

506
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:24,196
- Here.
- Hold on, hold on, let me see.

507
00:24:24,221 --> 00:24:25,236
Open your eye.

508
00:24:27,618 --> 00:24:28,778
How is it? Okay?

509
00:24:30,625 --> 00:24:31,833
- One more.
- Huh?! There’s still–

510
00:24:31,858 --> 00:24:34,207
One more. Don’t– open it, open it.

511
00:24:38,156 --> 00:24:39,156
Okay now?

512
00:24:39,809 --> 00:24:41,483
There! All good!

513
00:24:41,508 --> 00:24:42,508
It’s all good now.

514
00:24:42,597 --> 00:24:44,131
- Okay!
- Thank you.

515
00:24:44,168 --> 00:24:45,365
No problem, no problem!

516
00:24:45,390 --> 00:24:47,095
I thought something
serious happened to you!

517
00:24:49,023 --> 00:24:50,049
You’re so handsome!

518
00:24:50,397 --> 00:24:53,550
Wow, you look amazing here, Aga.

519
00:24:53,866 --> 00:24:58,518
Wow, but this doesn’t mean
anything to you, right?

520
00:24:58,633 --> 00:25:00,633
- Nothing. Nothing!
- Oh, it’s fine?

521
00:25:00,713 --> 00:25:01,713
Want me to show you?

522
00:25:01,738 --> 00:25:03,718
Okay, look. You’re so handsome!
You really are!

523
00:25:03,797 --> 00:25:04,817
What picture is that?

524
00:25:06,829 --> 00:25:09,268
- Aga looks so handsome!
- Really?!

525
00:25:09,293 --> 00:25:11,004
Oh, but this means
nothing, okay? Nothing.

526
00:25:11,029 --> 00:25:12,029
Alright!

527
00:25:13,143 --> 00:25:15,150
Oh! My husband looks
so handsome there, huh!

528
00:25:15,901 --> 00:25:18,567
Oh, but this doesn’t mean
anything to you, right? It’s okay?

529
00:25:18,664 --> 00:25:20,897
Oh, it doesn’t mean anything at all!
Who took that picture?

530
00:25:21,054 --> 00:25:23,041
I just found it lying around!

531
00:25:24,598 --> 00:25:26,117
- My love!
- But this doesn’t mean anything–

532
00:25:26,188 --> 00:25:29,007
My love, wait!
She just got something in her eye,

533
00:25:29,031 --> 00:25:31,851
I blew on it to help her, that’s all!

534
00:25:31,876 --> 00:25:32,876
I didn’t… I didn’t…

535
00:25:33,604 --> 00:25:36,137
You look so handsome
there, right, my love?

536
00:25:36,162 --> 00:25:37,850
My love, my love…

537
00:25:38,312 --> 00:25:40,003
- Oh, why? What?
- My love…

538
00:25:40,198 --> 00:25:41,198
You’re so handsome!

539
00:25:41,758 --> 00:25:42,758
My love!

540
00:25:44,325 --> 00:25:45,525
Amazing!

541
00:25:45,838 --> 00:25:46,958
You’re great!

542
00:25:49,583 --> 00:25:51,556
Wait, my love!

543
00:25:51,581 --> 00:25:52,581
- My love!
- Yes, what is it?

544
00:25:52,614 --> 00:25:54,152
- What?
- What do you mean, what?!

545
00:25:56,542 --> 00:25:57,542
It’s true!

546
00:25:57,819 --> 00:25:58,819
That picture, okay?!

547
00:25:58,994 --> 00:26:05,910
Mika had something in her eye,
and of course, that hurts, right?!

548
00:26:05,935 --> 00:26:08,806
So I helped her out! That’s it!

549
00:26:08,865 --> 00:26:10,265
The picture just caught that moment.

550
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:11,500
That’s all!

551
00:26:12,802 --> 00:26:14,295
So it’s true!

552
00:26:15,170 --> 00:26:17,384
Yes, it’s true, but I didn’t do
anything wrong!

553
00:26:17,408 --> 00:26:19,070
Don’t get mad at me!

554
00:26:19,198 --> 00:26:22,032
Who said I was mad?

555
00:26:22,063 --> 00:26:23,502
You’re mad. I know you.

556
00:26:23,555 --> 00:26:25,215
You’re not talking to me.

557
00:26:25,248 --> 00:26:27,547
- Am I not talking to you?
- So, you’re not mad?

558
00:26:27,572 --> 00:26:28,971
- Did you do anything wrong?
- I didn’t!

559
00:26:29,008 --> 00:26:30,897
Well, there you go.
If you didn’t do anything wrong,

560
00:26:30,921 --> 00:26:32,762
why are you explaining so much?

561
00:26:32,787 --> 00:26:33,787
Exactly!

562
00:26:34,399 --> 00:26:35,399
That’s what I’m saying!

563
00:26:36,474 --> 00:26:37,521
Hey, you guys!

564
00:26:38,474 --> 00:26:40,494
Give me back my spatula!

565
00:26:40,856 --> 00:26:41,856
But, Dad –

566
00:26:41,881 --> 00:26:43,542
Don’t “but, Dad” me!

567
00:26:43,567 --> 00:26:44,819
And you?

568
00:26:46,403 --> 00:26:47,551
Just think about it.

569
00:26:48,209 --> 00:26:52,224
Return my spatula,
and that’s the end of the story!

570
00:26:52,249 --> 00:26:53,601
- Spatula. Spatula.
- Okay?

571
00:26:53,654 --> 00:26:54,654
Spatula.

572
00:26:55,208 --> 00:26:56,401
Spa-tu-la!

573
00:26:57,214 --> 00:26:59,172
- My loves!
- My love!

574
00:27:00,405 --> 00:27:01,405
You’re not mad, right?

575
00:27:01,430 --> 00:27:03,111
I’m not mad,
what’s wrong with you?!

576
00:27:07,958 --> 00:27:09,372
Don’t worry, everyone.

577
00:27:09,748 --> 00:27:12,847
You know, he’s just like that,
but I’m sure tomorrow,

578
00:27:12,872 --> 00:27:15,373
he’ll be happy
with your surprise.

579
00:27:17,918 --> 00:27:22,716
Wait, what’s happening
tomorrow again? I forgot.

580
00:27:22,861 --> 00:27:24,701
Dad’s birthday is tomorrow.

581
00:27:24,756 --> 00:27:27,006
- Oh yeah, it’s his birthday–
- Ssssssshhhhhh–

582
00:27:27,031 --> 00:27:28,237
–Aga’s birthday.

583
00:27:32,947 --> 00:27:34,273
470 pesos?

584
00:27:35,088 --> 00:27:36,368
That’s a lot.

585
00:27:37,848 --> 00:27:39,148
What if we go on a trip instead?

586
00:27:39,633 --> 00:27:42,820
Outing? Come on! Let’s go!

587
00:27:44,548 --> 00:27:47,614
You’re so smart, so bright.
You’re like one gig of memory!

588
00:27:47,729 --> 00:27:50,309
Thank you so much, sister,
just like you!

589
00:27:50,404 --> 00:27:52,517
Wait, how are we going to prepare for Aga?

590
00:27:52,542 --> 00:27:54,099
How about you join a marathon, Cap?

591
00:27:54,124 --> 00:27:55,712
Not now, I’m too lazy!

592
00:27:57,504 --> 00:28:00,977
Chef K, your smile is so nice!

593
00:28:01,072 --> 00:28:04,225
You look so handsome,
especially when you smile!

594
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:08,779
Is it because you saw me
in my outing outfit?

595
00:28:09,597 --> 00:28:11,295
I don’t know about Uncle K,

596
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:14,550
he’s been pacing around like
he’s walking on clouds!

597
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:16,150
Why?

598
00:28:16,431 --> 00:28:17,844
Can’t I be happy?

599
00:28:18,222 --> 00:28:19,649
I just want to throw a party!

600
00:28:20,053 --> 00:28:21,626
- A party?
- Oh, a party?!

601
00:28:21,651 --> 00:28:23,452
Chef K, perfect!

602
00:28:23,477 --> 00:28:26,747
We’re throwing a party for Kuya Aga!

603
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:29,159
- Just in time!
- Look at that luck!

604
00:28:29,366 --> 00:28:30,626
- Aga?
- Yes!

605
00:28:30,745 --> 00:28:31,805
Alright, I’ll dance!

606
00:28:32,558 --> 00:28:33,558
Hmmm…

607
00:28:33,784 --> 00:28:34,858
But Chef K,

608
00:28:35,626 --> 00:28:38,072
this is all we could gather—470 pesos.

609
00:28:38,172 --> 00:28:40,692
Oh, no problem!

610
00:28:41,034 --> 00:28:42,087
Don’t worry about it!

611
00:28:42,595 --> 00:28:44,129
I’ll take care of it!

612
00:28:45,572 --> 00:28:47,204
Thank you, Chef K!

613
00:28:47,229 --> 00:28:49,189
Are you feeling feverish?

614
00:28:49,214 --> 00:28:50,415
Big time, big time!

615
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:52,834
What fever?!
I said I’ve got this!

616
00:28:53,212 --> 00:28:54,412
Don’t worry about anything.

617
00:28:54,437 --> 00:28:56,325
Sky’s the limit!

618
00:28:57,816 --> 00:29:00,314
Really, Chef K?!

619
00:29:00,354 --> 00:29:02,078
What do you think, I’m joking?

620
00:29:02,103 --> 00:29:05,458
Go ahead, order!
I want it extravagant!

621
00:29:06,964 --> 00:29:09,370
Cook everything!
Chef K will pay for it!

622
00:29:09,395 --> 00:29:11,864
Bring it all! I’ll call now!

623
00:29:11,889 --> 00:29:12,889
Cook it!

624
00:29:14,163 --> 00:29:15,470
We’ve got sales coming in!

625
00:29:17,625 --> 00:29:18,625
This…

626
00:29:19,344 --> 00:29:20,344
Oh?

627
00:29:24,372 --> 00:29:25,531
- I’m leaving.
- I’m leaving.

628
00:29:25,556 --> 00:29:27,102
- What? You’re leaving too?
- What? You’re leaving too?

629
00:29:27,649 --> 00:29:29,462
Wait, wait, wait.

630
00:29:30,197 --> 00:29:31,863
Don’t talk all at once;
you’re confusing me.

631
00:29:31,888 --> 00:29:32,888
What’s going on?

632
00:29:32,913 --> 00:29:38,443
Ah, Ate Cha, Kuya Aga, I’m sorry for
trying to cause a rift between you two.

633
00:29:38,765 --> 00:29:39,791
What?

634
00:29:41,009 --> 00:29:43,176
So, Iskineport was
telling me the truth?

635
00:29:44,967 --> 00:29:48,207
Yes, it’s true.
Iskineport wasn’t peeping on me.

636
00:29:48,384 --> 00:29:50,464
Well, maybe once.

637
00:29:50,489 --> 00:29:52,326
What I mean is,

638
00:29:52,649 --> 00:29:56,936
I was only ordered to make
Ate Cha jealous of you, Kuya Aga.

639
00:29:57,653 --> 00:29:58,653
W-what?

640
00:29:58,664 --> 00:30:00,137
W-who told you to do that?

641
00:30:03,102 --> 00:30:04,133
Ah…him!

642
00:30:04,158 --> 00:30:07,169
He told me to do it
to pay off my debt!

643
00:30:07,194 --> 00:30:08,659
What?! Chef K?!

644
00:30:08,684 --> 00:30:09,684
Chef K?!

645
00:30:09,709 --> 00:30:11,922
Wait, wait! Calm down, everyone!

646
00:30:12,169 --> 00:30:13,391
- What’s this about?
- Is it true

647
00:30:13,416 --> 00:30:15,972
you planned to make
my loves and me fight?

648
00:30:15,997 --> 00:30:16,997
Me?!

649
00:30:17,094 --> 00:30:18,094
Yes!

650
00:30:18,338 --> 00:30:20,778
- You!
- Well… yes, yes, it’s true!

651
00:30:20,893 --> 00:30:22,221
- What?!
- What do you mean, yes?!

652
00:30:22,246 --> 00:30:26,309
I was behind it,
but it wasn’t to make you fight.

653
00:30:26,884 --> 00:30:32,567
- Then… what for?
- To prove your loyalty to each other.

654
00:30:33,374 --> 00:30:35,523
And you proved it!

655
00:30:36,630 --> 00:30:37,630
You passed!

656
00:30:38,623 --> 00:30:42,349
Happy birthday, Kuya Aga!

657
00:30:43,563 --> 00:30:46,196
What…? Seriously?!

658
00:30:47,567 --> 00:30:48,860
Happy birthday!

659
00:30:48,885 --> 00:30:51,680
Happy birthday!

660
00:30:51,756 --> 00:30:53,663
I’m telling you, it’s simple!

661
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:56,644
And I had nothing to do with that!

662
00:30:56,893 --> 00:30:58,323
Actually, Kuya Aga,

663
00:30:58,347 --> 00:31:02,614
we all chipped in for this,
but Chef K really covered most of it.

664
00:31:02,798 --> 00:31:04,512
What?! Chef K?!

665
00:31:04,744 --> 00:31:06,694
Chef K?! Is that true?!

666
00:31:06,719 --> 00:31:09,485
Oh, and here I thought you were
accusing me of something bad!

667
00:31:09,643 --> 00:31:11,823
No, don’t take it the wrong way!
Stop sulking now!

668
00:31:11,848 --> 00:31:12,848
I don’t want to…

669
00:31:12,935 --> 00:31:16,632
Come on, let it go! It’s fine now.
Stop sulking. It’s all good, we’re good!

670
00:31:16,670 --> 00:31:19,767
- Kiss… kiss!
- I don’t want to!

671
00:31:19,944 --> 00:31:21,098
Speech!

672
00:31:22,271 --> 00:31:23,271
Speech!

673
00:31:23,282 --> 00:31:31,410
Okay, fine… Honestly, I don’t know
what to say. I’m so overwhelmed right now.

674
00:31:33,275 --> 00:31:35,967
But what I want to say
is that I definitely didn’t

675
00:31:35,991 --> 00:31:39,068
make a mistake choosing
this place to raise my family.

676
00:31:39,559 --> 00:31:49,418
Of course, I’m grateful to Lola Maxi,
Iskineport, Chard, and my BFF, Chef K.

677
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:50,680
Oh, you’re all the same.

678
00:31:51,147 --> 00:31:54,978
No way, come on!
You know we love you!

679
00:31:55,947 --> 00:32:02,683
And I’m also thankful for all my friends
and neighbors here in this barangay!

680
00:32:02,885 --> 00:32:05,079
Thank you, everyone!

681
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,688
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

682
00:32:06,713 --> 00:32:07,713
Yay!

683
00:32:09,050 --> 00:32:12,471
Aga, Aga, Aga, Aga!

684
00:32:12,526 --> 00:32:17,925
If you ask me where the best
place to celebrate my birthday is,

685
00:32:18,205 --> 00:32:22,433
there’s no better place
than Barangay Singko.

686
00:32:22,994 --> 00:32:24,481
Thank you!

687
00:32:24,874 --> 00:32:27,500
I love you all! Let’s eat!

688
00:32:31,041 --> 00:32:32,607
Happy birthday!

689
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,867
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

690
00:32:37,026 --> 00:32:41,392
Happy birthday to you!

691
00:32:41,417 --> 00:32:42,651
Thank you!

692
00:32:42,790 --> 00:32:44,164
Happy birthday!

693
00:32:44,366 --> 00:32:45,780
Make a wish!

694
00:32:46,060 --> 00:32:47,060
Okay!

695
00:32:47,728 --> 00:32:49,441
Yay!

696
00:32:49,466 --> 00:32:50,885
Happy birthday!

697
00:32:50,910 --> 00:32:53,904
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

698
00:32:53,935 --> 00:32:55,863
- Happy birthday!
- Thank you, thank you, thank you!

699
00:32:55,888 --> 00:32:59,902
Dad, happy birthday!

700
00:32:59,927 --> 00:33:03,111
Wow! What’s this? Huh?!

701
00:33:05,104 --> 00:33:06,104
Open it!

702
00:33:06,119 --> 00:33:08,119
It’s our gift to you!

703
00:33:08,260 --> 00:33:10,167
Happy birthday, Dad, we love you!

704
00:33:10,192 --> 00:33:11,591
Wow!

705
00:33:12,923 --> 00:33:15,263
My loves, hold this for me, will you?
Let me check it out!

706
00:33:19,016 --> 00:33:22,396
Oh, wow!

707
00:33:22,783 --> 00:33:27,923
This is amazing!

708
00:33:28,157 --> 00:33:29,616
You got this made for me?

709
00:33:29,641 --> 00:33:31,522
It’s our gift!

710
00:33:32,711 --> 00:33:33,751
Yes, right?

711
00:33:33,964 --> 00:33:35,167
- Yes!
- I told you,

712
00:33:35,192 --> 00:33:37,387
old things are valuable when restored.

713
00:33:37,727 --> 00:33:42,050
Thank you, Andres, Atasha, Lola
Maxi, my loves—thank you so much.

714
00:33:42,381 --> 00:33:48,417
You know, like the philosophy of kintsugi,
the art of embracing damage.

715
00:33:48,897 --> 00:33:55,664
When you value imperfections,
they become beautiful.

716
00:33:55,689 --> 00:33:58,665
Like this—it was broken,
but you fixed it,

717
00:33:58,690 --> 00:34:04,421
and now it’s even more meaningful
because you didn’t throw it away.

718
00:34:04,446 --> 00:34:08,140
It’s the same with people, right?

719
00:34:08,165 --> 00:34:09,681
Imperfections make them unique,
just like Iskineport here,

720
00:34:09,706 --> 00:34:11,734
who’s practically damaged goods.

721
00:34:13,685 --> 00:34:15,151
- What did you say?
- Nothing, I said I love you!

722
00:34:15,176 --> 00:34:16,511
Thanks. I love you too.

723
00:34:16,536 --> 00:34:18,890
Yeah, see Iskineport, he’s an example.
You can see how damaged he is.

724
00:34:19,232 --> 00:34:21,904
See, even Chef K—
he causes so much damage.

725
00:34:21,929 --> 00:34:22,929
What?! Me?!

726
00:34:23,122 --> 00:34:26,182
Chef K, I mean I’ve caused you
a lot of trouble.

727
00:34:26,715 --> 00:34:28,819
- Oh.
- And yet you still love me, right?

728
00:34:30,351 --> 00:34:32,011
So that’s what I mean.

729
00:34:32,036 --> 00:34:36,481
Anyway, thank you so much again,
Lola Maxi, Atasha,

730
00:34:38,463 --> 00:34:43,392
Andres–the boy who
always shivers, my love!

731
00:34:45,031 --> 00:34:46,644
Woohoo!

732
00:34:47,552 --> 00:34:49,112
Enough yapping, let’s eat!

733
00:34:49,137 --> 00:34:51,125
Yay!

734
00:34:51,150 --> 00:34:52,616
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

735
00:34:53,608 --> 00:34:55,462
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

736
00:34:55,887 --> 00:34:59,953
Aww, this is the most
memorable birthday ever.

737
00:35:00,189 --> 00:35:02,356
So much happened, right?

738
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:03,760
Exactly!

739
00:35:03,785 --> 00:35:10,796
Love, loyalty,
and kintsugi win in the end!

740
00:35:12,141 --> 00:35:13,974
- That’s right, that’s right!
- Oh!

741
00:35:14,060 --> 00:35:15,433
- Yes!
- Say hello!

742
00:35:15,458 --> 00:35:16,801
- Hello there!
- Hello!

743
00:35:16,826 --> 00:35:22,718
And remember, there’s so much more
to learn from our generation.

744
00:35:23,329 --> 00:35:26,235
But Gen Z is okay too.

745
00:35:26,859 --> 00:35:27,859
Gen Z?

746
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:33,361
Sure, but Gen X
is different—

747
00:35:34,599 --> 00:35:38,539
we’re tough and we never give up.

748
00:35:38,933 --> 00:35:40,753
Hold on, hold on!

749
00:35:40,778 --> 00:35:47,564
No matter what generation you’re from,
the most important thing is…

750
00:35:48,317 --> 00:35:54,317
In struggles and joy,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!

751
00:35:54,342 --> 00:35:55,884
Bye-bye!

752
00:35:55,909 --> 00:35:56,909
See you!

753
00:35:56,922 --> 00:36:00,622
I was thinking—we should
make our bakery open 24 hours.

754
